<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Miscreant" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Miscreant,</orth> a vile wretch: <cit><quote>thou art a traitor and a m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 1.1.39" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 1, 39</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>well, m., I'll be there as soon as you,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.4.44" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 4, 44</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>curse, m., when thou comest to the stake,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.44" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 44</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>O vassal, m.!</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.163" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 163</bibl></cit> (Qq <emph>recreant</emph>).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>